    <body>
      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes">
          <link target="#spp-875-06E2-footnote-title-1 #spp-875-06E2-title-1"/>
        </linkGrp>
        <div n="875-06E2">
          <head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-875-06E2-headnote-1">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-875-06E2-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-06E2-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">Written in the year 1729.&#13;</l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-875-06E2-headnote-2">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-875-06E2-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-06E2-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-875-06E2-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-875-06E2-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-06E2-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-1" n="1"><hi rend="display-initial">W</hi>E give the world to understand,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-2" n="2">Our thriving Dean has purchas'd land;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-3" n="3">A purchase which will bring him clear</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-4" n="4">Above his rent four pounds a-year;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-5" n="5">Provided, to improve the ground,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-6" n="6">He will but add two hundred pound,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-7" n="7">And from his endless hoarded store</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-8" n="8">To build a house five hundred more.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-9" n="9">Sir Arthur <note place="foot">·Sir Arthur Acheson, from whom the purchase was made.</note> too shall have his will,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-10" n="10">And  call the mansion <hi rend="italics">Drapier's hill</hi>:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-11" n="11">That when a nation, long inslav'd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-12" n="12">Forgets by whom it once was sav'd;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-13" n="13">When none the D<hi rend="small-caps">RAPIER</hi>'s praise shall sing;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-14" n="14">His signs aloft no longer swing;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-15" n="15">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-16" n="16">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-17" n="17">His medals and his prints forgotten,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-18" n="18">And all his handkerchiefs are rotten<note place="foot">·Medals were cast, many signs hung up, and handkerchiefs made with devices, in honour of the author, under the name of <hi rend="italics">M.B. Drapier</hi>.</note>;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-19" n="19">His famous L<hi rend="small-caps">ETTERS</hi> made waste paper;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-20" n="20">This hill may keep the name of D<hi rend="small-caps">RAPIER</hi>:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-21" n="21">In spite of envy flourish still,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-06E2-line-22" n="22">And D<hi rend="small-caps">RAPIER</hi>'s vie with C<hi rend="small-caps">OOPER</hi>'s hill.</l>
          </lg>
        </div>
      </div>
